# MASVEL AI PRO — Deployment Guide

## ⚠️ CRITICAL FIRST STEP
Your HF token was shared in chat. **Revoke it immediately:**
→ https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
Generate a new one with **Inference API (read)** permission only.

---

## Project Structure

```
masvel-deploy/
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py              ← FastAPI app (deploy to Render)
│   ├── requirements.txt     ← Python dependencies
│   ├── render.yaml          ← Render config
│   ├── .env.example         ← Template — copy to .env locally
│   └── .gitignore           ← Keeps .env out of Git
│
└── frontend/
    ├── index.html           ← Your full site (deploy to Netlify)
    └── netlify.toml         ← Netlify headers config
```

---

## Step 1 — Deploy Backend to Render

1. Push `backend/` folder to a **new GitHub repo** (e.g. `masvel-backend`)
2. Go to https://render.com → New → Web Service
3. Connect your GitHub repo
4. Set these values:
   - **Build Command:** `pip install -r requirements.txt`
   - **Start Command:** `uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT`
   - **Runtime:** Python 3
5. Under **Environment → Environment Variables**, add:
   - `HUGGINGFACE_TOKEN` = your new HF token
   - `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` = `https://your-site.netlify.app`
     (you'll fill this after Netlify deploy — use `*` temporarily)
6. Deploy. Copy your Render URL (e.g. `https://masvel-ai-backend.onrender.com`)

---

## Step 2 — Update Frontend URL

Open `frontend/index.html` and find this line (around line 2390):

```js
const MASVEL_BACKEND_URL = "https://YOUR_RENDER_APP.onrender.com/generate-masvel-image";
```

Replace `YOUR_RENDER_APP` with your actual Render service name.

---

## Step 3 — Deploy Frontend to Netlify

1. Push `frontend/` folder to a **new GitHub repo** (e.g. `masvel-frontend`)
2. Go to https://netlify.com → Add new site → Import from Git
3. Set **Publish directory** to `.` (root)
4. Deploy. Copy your Netlify URL (e.g. `https://masvelai.netlify.app`)
5. Go back to Render → Environment Variables → Update `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` with your Netlify URL

---

## Step 4 — Local Testing (optional)

```bash
cd backend
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env — add your real HUGGINGFACE_TOKEN
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn main:app --reload
# API now at http://localhost:8000
# Test: curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/generate-masvel-image \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"prompt":"a golden sunset over mountains"}'
```

---

## Notes

- **Cold start delay:** Render free tier sleeps after 15min. First request may take ~30s.
- **Model warmup:** SDXL on HF free inference also has cold start. Error 503 = retrying is fine.
- **Rate limit:** Backend limits each IP to 5 requests per 60 seconds.
- **Token safety:** Never commit `.env`. Never paste the token in any file pushed to Git.